cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the controllability of multi-agent systems, which is a topic related to control theory and systems engineering. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph theory and network analysis, which are relevant to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.DS (Dynamical Systems). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach to study controllability, which could be of interest to researchers in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
